postcontent:
This is a Ruger 10/22 semi-auto rifle converted into a PS90 that accepts .22LR. For sale is the original Ruger 10/22, original Ruger 10/22 stock, HTA 90/22 PS90 imitation stock, 4 Butler creek steel lip 25 round magazines, 2 Ruger brand 25-round magazines, discreet carrying case, and one factory Ruger 10 round magazine.  I also ordered and installed the extended magazine release and extended bolt open arms. These are part of the Ruger 10/22 but can be uninstalled easily. They make magazine changes much easier than when using the default/standard Ruger factory release mechanisms.

The Ruger rifle can be removed from the HTA hardware at will and returned to its original form. I am willing to sell the HTA stock alone but not the Ruger alone. Willing to throw in a box of ammo at the right price. I've fired maybe 600 rounds through this. Very reliable with solid point bullets or copper jacketed stuff. Some failures to feed with very soft lead tips (as on Armscor or crappy Winchester ammo). The HTA stock has a tri-rail at the front for mounting the sites of your choice. I have personally been using a red dot sight but pretty much anything would go. Price shown does not include the red dot.

The suppressor is fake and removable (you can run with the Ruger barrel showing if desired). The rifle is NOT an SBR in the HTA stock, it is legal standard length both total length and barrel length. There is a safety at the HTA trigger and also the actual ruger safety is accessible as well. The Ruger charging handle can be pulled, or there is an ambidextrous charging handle that you can use to chamber a round.

I take good care of my things. Nothing wrong with any of this stuff but need the cash and not using this much. I have all the boxes, manuals, etc., from both the Ruger and the HTA stock purchases. Also a few extra hardware parts and the instructions for assembly/disassembly.
